com.pb.sawdust.util

Class FilterChain<I>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.pb.sawdust.util.FilterChain<I>
  • Type Parameters:
    I - The type of input which this class filters.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    Filter<I>

    public class FilterChain<I>
extends java.lang.Object
implements Filter<I>
    The FilterChain class is used to combine many filters into a single, composite filter. The order that filters are added to a filter chain determines the order that they are applied when filtering.

    • Method Detail

      • addFilter

        public Filter<I> addFilter(Filter<I> filter)
        Add a filter to this filter chain. This filter will be added to the "end" of the chain; that is, calls to filter(I) will only call this filter if the input passes all other (previously added) filters.
        Parameters:
        filter - The filter to add to this filter chain.
        Returns:
        this filter chain.

      • filter

        public boolean filter(I input)
        Filter the given input. A return value of true indicates the input has passed the filter, while a value of false indicates rejection. This method will sequentially apply the filters held by this filter chain in the order they were added. This is a short-circuiting filtering process: if any filter in the chain fails (returns false), then this method will return false without applying any of the subsequent filters in the chain.
        Specified by:
        filter in interface Filter<I>
        Parameters:
        input - The input to be filtered.
        Returns:
        true if input passes the filter, false otherwise.
